Class ParsingStoreSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.guardtime.envelope.packaging.parsing.ParsingStoreSession

  • public class ParsingStoreSession

    Keeps track of content passed to ParsingStore and allows for easier retrieval of such content.

      • store

        public void store(String name,
                  InputStream input)
           throws ParsingStoreException
        Stores provided data at key into ParsingStore.
        Parameters:
        name - the key at which to store the data; usually a filename.
        input - data to be stored.
        Throws:
        ParsingStoreException - When an error occurs storing the data. Can also mean that the key is already in use. Good practice is to test with contains(String). Since generally each ParsingStoreSession should be used for one envelope parsing there shouldn't occur any duplicate keys.
